\int_0^{\pi/2} x^2\sin(x)\,dx
u=x^2
dv=\sin(x)
x^2-\cos(x)+2\int x\cos(x)\,dx.\quad
u=x
dv=\cos(x).
x^2-\cos(x)+2[x-\sin(x)-\int\sin(x)]
x^2-\cos(x)+-2 \sin(x)(x)-\cos(x)\Big|_0^{\pi/2} =\dfrac{\pi^2}{4}-0-2
\begin{align} \int_0^{\pi/2} x^2\sin(x)\,dx & = -x^2\cos(x)+2\int x\cos(x)\,dx \\ \\  & = -x^2 \cos x + 2\Big[x \sin x - \int \sin x\,dx\Big]\\ \\ & = -x^2\cos x + 2x \sin x - (-2\cos x)\\ \\ & = -x^2 \cos x + 2x \sin x + 2\cos x \Big|_0^{2\pi}\end{align}
